00:28:12.040 --> 00:28:15.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.
Well, that was wonderful to share in.

00:28:15.877 --> 00:28:17.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now they’re graduates.

00:28:17.479 --> 00:28:21.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
So at this time, we’re pleased to present

00:28:21.649 --> 00:28:25.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
the graduates of the 151st class of Gilead.

00:28:42.837 --> 00:28:44.839 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s a lot of love here today.

00:28:44.839 --> 00:28:46.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s wonderful.

00:28:46.908 --> 00:28:50.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we have a letter to be presented

00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:53.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
by one of the now graduates
of the 151st class.

00:28:53.915 --> 00:28:57.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Davide Vita

00:28:57.719 --> 00:29:00.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
from Italy and going to Albania
will read that now at this time.

00:29:07.295 --> 00:29:10.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
“To the Governing Body and Bethel family.

00:29:10.231 --> 00:29:13.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Dear Brothers: For the past five months,

00:29:13.868 --> 00:29:18.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we have traveled through the Bible
from the first page to the last.

00:29:18.106 --> 00:29:21.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We experienced the heat of the Sinai

00:29:21.376 --> 00:29:25.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and found ourselves
in the depths of the Red Sea,

00:29:25.547 --> 00:29:28.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
“in the narrow alleys of Jerusalem,

00:29:28.716 --> 00:29:31.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and high up on Mount Hermon.

00:29:31.820 --> 00:29:36.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We met the prophets, visited the temple,

00:29:36.191 --> 00:29:39.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
“saw the awesome celestial chariot,

00:29:39.561 --> 00:29:44.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and enjoyed the precious company
of Jesus and the apostles.

00:29:44.432 --> 00:29:47.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
“What is the result of our journey?

00:29:47.535 --> 00:29:50.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The very same that resulted for Job

00:29:50.805 --> 00:29:55.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
“after he encountered his God
—great astonishment!

00:29:55.243 --> 00:29:59.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Although he recognized
that he would only be able to understand

00:29:59.781 --> 00:30:02.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘just the fringes of his ways,’

00:30:02.283 --> 00:30:06.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
“it was enough to make him marvel at Jehovah.

00:30:06.054 --> 00:30:10.325 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Now I know
that you are able to do all things.’

00:30:10.325 --> 00:30:14.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
“At the same time,
the experience humbled him

00:30:14.329 --> 00:30:17.398 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that he
‘put [his] hand over [his] mouth.’

00:30:17.398 --> 00:30:20.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
“That is how we feel today.

00:30:20.735 --> 00:30:23.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Gilead leaves us in its wake,

00:30:23.705 --> 00:30:27.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
“filled with awe, humility, and gratitude.

00:30:27.942 --> 00:30:32.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Studying the Bible
is studying about Jehovah himself.

00:30:32.380 --> 00:30:35.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And what we have learned
has impressed on our hearts

00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:39.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the depth of Jehovah’s love
for each one of his servants.

00:30:40.922 --> 00:30:44.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We saw this love
not only in numerous Bible accounts

00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:47.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but in those who imitate him
and his Son, Jesus

00:30:47.729 --> 00:30:51.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
“—the Governing Body, our guest instructors,

00:30:51.633 --> 00:30:55.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
“our Gilead instructors,
and the Bethel family

00:30:55.403 --> 00:30:58.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
“here at Patterson and the other complexes.

00:30:58.907 --> 00:31:01.676 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Your example is the living answer

00:31:01.676 --> 00:31:05.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to the question of how
to define Christian love.

00:31:05.613 --> 00:31:09.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We express our heartfelt thanks
to you, the Governing Body,

00:31:09.918 --> 00:31:13.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and all those who made
this unforgettable experience possible.

00:31:15.023 --> 00:31:19.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We know that our divine education
is not our possession alone.

00:31:19.627 --> 00:31:21.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
“We received it to share it.

00:31:21.829 --> 00:31:26.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The end of Gilead School
for our class is the close of a chapter.

00:31:26.734 --> 00:31:31.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And we are determined
to write the next chapter of our story

00:31:31.472 --> 00:31:33.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
“by showing the same love

00:31:33.575 --> 00:31:36.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and personal interest we have experienced.

00:31:36.711 --> 00:31:41.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It is our prayer that as we apply
what we have been taught,

00:31:41.716 --> 00:31:46.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
“we inspire others
and make Jehovah’s heart rejoice.

00:31:46.588 --> 00:31:51.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As the psalmist expressed at Psalm 106:48:

00:31:51.159 --> 00:31:56.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘May Jehovah . . . be praised
throughout all eternity. . . . Praise Jah!’

00:31:57.065 --> 00:32:02.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your brothers and sisters,
the 151st class of Gilead.”

00:32:11.379 --> 00:32:13.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you for that beautiful letter.

00:32:13.815 --> 00:32:18.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
And those heartfelt expressions
are something we will remember too.

00:32:19.821 --> 00:32:22.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, in closing,
we just have a few things to say to you now.

00:32:22.690 --> 00:32:24.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
You are graduates

00:32:24.726 --> 00:32:28.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
—graduates of the 151st class of Gilead.

00:32:28.229 --> 00:32:30.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
I used the word “students”
a few times earlier on

00:32:30.598 --> 00:32:32.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
because you didn’t have
a diploma in hand yet.

00:32:32.634 --> 00:32:34.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now you have them.

00:32:34.435 --> 00:32:37.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s just such an encouraging
and wonderful thing to see.

00:32:37.805 --> 00:32:40.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
You may know that back in 2011,

00:32:40.875 --> 00:32:43.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Governing Body adjusted the objective

00:32:43.678 --> 00:32:46.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Gilead School training a bit.

00:32:46.147 --> 00:32:48.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now the training is even more focused

00:32:48.816 --> 00:32:50.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
on strengthening and stabilizing

00:32:50.885 --> 00:32:54.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
the field and branch organization.

00:32:54.088 --> 00:32:56.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since that time, a good number of graduates

00:32:56.391 --> 00:33:00.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
have been appointed to a Branch
or a Country Committee.

00:33:00.628 --> 00:33:04.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so with Jehovah’s blessing,
the training is working.

00:33:04.298 --> 00:33:06.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
But not all graduates from Gilead

00:33:06.534 --> 00:33:11.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
are brothers who may someday receive
such responsibilities.

00:33:11.539 --> 00:33:15.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have many sisters
in each class too, don’t we?

00:33:15.076 --> 00:33:17.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
So then, how might the goal

00:33:17.111 --> 00:33:21.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
of strengthening and stabilizing
the field and branch organization

00:33:21.315 --> 00:33:23.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
be reached through each one of you

00:33:23.584 --> 00:33:26.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
graduating brothers and sisters?

00:33:26.821 --> 00:33:31.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the goal is reached
when others can look at what you do and say

00:33:31.826 --> 00:33:35.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they see a man or woman of strong faith.

00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:39.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just as Paul wrote at 1 Thessalonians 1:8,

00:33:39.667 --> 00:33:41.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
where he said in part:

00:33:41.869 --> 00:33:45.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Not only has the word of [God]
sounded out from you . . .

00:33:45.406 --> 00:33:47.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but your faith in God

00:33:47.442 --> 00:33:50.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
has spread abroad in every place.”

00:33:50.778 --> 00:33:53.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s exactly what happens, isn’t it?

00:33:53.281 --> 00:33:56.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, such examples are priceless.

00:33:56.417 --> 00:33:59.821 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your schooling was designed
to strengthen your faith,

00:33:59.821 --> 00:34:02.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re confident
that it has done just that.

00:34:02.256 --> 00:34:04.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
You are ready for what is ahead.

00:34:04.792 --> 00:34:07.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our faith keeps us strong, though.

00:34:07.128 --> 00:34:10.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
And at 1 John 5:4,
the apostle John wrote:

00:34:10.098 --> 00:34:13.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
“This is the conquest
that has conquered the world,

00:34:13.468 --> 00:34:16.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
our faith,” right?

00:34:16.504 --> 00:34:19.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
With that in mind, for just a few minutes

00:34:19.340 --> 00:34:22.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
let’s consider
how you can keep your faith strong

00:34:22.376 --> 00:34:24.378 line:90% position:50% align:center
when you get to your assignments,

00:34:24.378 --> 00:34:28.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that you can be
that powerful force for good

00:34:28.750 --> 00:34:32.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
in strengthening and stabilizing
the field and branch organization.

00:34:32.887 --> 00:34:37.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
So when you’re settled into your assignments,
perhaps with new responsibilities,

00:34:37.892 --> 00:34:41.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
remember to remain focused
on what is most important,

00:34:41.529 --> 00:34:44.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
namely, the doing of God’s will.

00:34:44.065 --> 00:34:48.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
What could cause a person
to forget this if not careful?

00:34:48.703 --> 00:34:53.174 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we get into danger
if we ever start to feel

00:34:53.174 --> 00:34:56.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
like we have achieved everything

00:34:56.110 --> 00:34:59.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we’ve wanted to achieve
as our spiritual goals.

00:34:59.814 --> 00:35:02.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, if we allow that to happen,

00:35:02.483 --> 00:35:05.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
our interest could turn to other things.

00:35:05.086 --> 00:35:07.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
We never want to allow that to happen.

00:35:07.021 --> 00:35:09.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to remain focused on Jehovah
—his work.

00:35:09.757 --> 00:35:14.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s always about Jehovah
and helping other people.

00:35:14.195 --> 00:35:18.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never become distracted
by losing sight of the need

00:35:18.599 --> 00:35:21.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep advancing spiritually day by day.

00:35:21.569 --> 00:35:25.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never become content with what
this empty system of things has to offer.

00:35:25.740 --> 00:35:29.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remain fixed on Jehovah’s promises
and on the doing of his will.

00:35:29.710 --> 00:35:34.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep your “large shield of faith” strong.

00:35:34.682 --> 00:35:39.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Bible times, soldiers
repaired their shields between battles.

00:35:39.153 --> 00:35:42.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
If a soldier found damage
or weakness to his shield,

00:35:42.924 --> 00:35:45.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
he diligently made the needed repairs.

00:35:45.993 --> 00:35:49.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this way, he was always ready
to fight the next battle.

00:35:49.997 --> 00:35:52.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
He never let down his guard.

00:35:52.099 --> 00:35:54.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
We need to keep this up in a spiritual way.

00:35:54.669 --> 00:35:59.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over time, a brother or sister
might lay down his or her shield of faith

00:35:59.540 --> 00:36:02.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
and go after things
that have no lasting value.

00:36:02.877 --> 00:36:07.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Devil wants nothing more
than to see us neglect our faith,

00:36:07.582 --> 00:36:11.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
because that will pull
everything down if he can do that.

00:36:11.752 --> 00:36:15.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
We show that we’re strengthening
our faith in God

00:36:15.122 --> 00:36:19.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we take time
to give attention to our spiritual need.

00:36:19.694 --> 00:36:21.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
The basics always count.

00:36:21.896 --> 00:36:24.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
The basics always count.

00:36:24.332 --> 00:36:28.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
So then be certain
to regularly attend Christian meetings

00:36:28.035 --> 00:36:31.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
(which we know you’ll do
and soon in person—right?),

00:36:31.572 --> 00:36:35.743 line:90% position:50% align:center
to zealously speak to others
about Jehovah’s name and his Kingdom,

00:36:35.743 --> 00:36:39.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
to maintain strong faith
by reading God’s Word every day,

00:36:39.914 --> 00:36:44.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then to apply its counsel
prayerfully in all that you do.

00:36:45.486 --> 00:36:48.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those are the basics that never fail us

00:36:48.155 --> 00:36:50.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
and help us to keep our faith strong.

00:36:50.791 --> 00:36:54.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in summary, don’t take liberties
with your spiritual routine

00:36:54.262 --> 00:36:57.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
now that you’ve graduated
from this wonderful, beautiful school.

00:36:57.431 --> 00:36:59.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never neglect those basic things.

00:36:59.533 --> 00:37:02.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never become self-satisfied
because of resting

00:37:02.770 --> 00:37:06.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
on a privilege that you may come to enjoy.

00:37:06.807 --> 00:37:10.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
And finally, keep growing as a godly person

00:37:10.444 --> 00:37:15.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
because you remember how kind
Jehovah has been to you and to all of us.

00:37:15.449 --> 00:37:18.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be like the diligent soldier who worked hard

00:37:18.753 --> 00:37:23.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
to care for that shield
and all of his vital armor.

00:37:23.391 --> 00:37:28.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
As you remain focused on what Gilead School
has now strengthened you to do,

00:37:28.195 --> 00:37:30.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
you will always be ready

00:37:30.464 --> 00:37:33.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
to “fight the fine fight of the faith.”

00:37:33.901 --> 00:37:38.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
As mentioned earlier, we have confidence
that you will do just that.

00:37:38.906 --> 00:37:42.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
May Jehovah and his dear Son bless you

00:37:42.410 --> 00:37:44.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
—each one of you—
for it.

